text.2:
The #COVID19 pandemic hasn’t been easy for many of us, particularly not young people. 
I am grateful to @SuperM for sharing their message of hope, positivity & kindness with us. 

I look forward to their performance on #WorldMentalHealthDay this Saturday!

#SuperMxWHO #SuperM https://t.co/cLulD9rdlm

:white_heavy_check_mark: Scaling up testing
:white_heavy_check_mark: Strengthening health care delivery system
:white_heavy_check_mark: Identifying & protecting vulnerable populations

:backhand_index_pointing_right: https://t.co/mDWN7EVWWr https://t.co/1QrD8E0NnS

:small_blue_diamond:Coordinating care
:small_blue_diamond:Advocating for their patients’ needs to health facility managers and policy-makers https://t.co/Nw7gGwsIiM

WHO ‘World Report on Vision’ provides :keycap_digit_one: evidence, :keycap_digit_two: effective strategies and :keycap_digit_three: recommendations to help countries boost their efforts in reducing the burden of eye conditions and vision impairment.

Download the full report :backhand_index_pointing_right:https://t.co/rBMMRsxcuJ https://t.co/zP7iRy5vBC

Universal Health Coverage includes the full spectrum of essential, quality health services:
:small_orange_diamond: Promotion
:small_orange_diamond: Prevention
:small_orange_diamond: Treatment
:small_orange_diamond: Rehabilitation
:small_orange_diamond: Palliative care https://t.co/63ZNqZUKtx
text.11: Delighted to speak at the #UNGA Ministerial Meeting with Foreign Ministers: :Japan: @moteging, :Georgia: @DZalkaliani, :Thailand: @PramudwinaiDon. I thank them for their leadership in delivering on the promise we made last year: #HealthForAll. #COVID19 makes this pledge more important than ever! https://t.co/na1o1nVl5q
text.12: Big thanks @moteging, :Japan: Foreign Minister, and the Government of #Japan for your generous contribution of USD 130 million to the COVAX Advance Market Commitment. @WHO welcomes your commitment and leadership in the fight against #COVID19. Solidarity! https://t.co/q1pUpgtFY5
text.13:
#COVID19 has highlighted the urgent need for strong primary health care that can provide essential services within the community - when and where people need it. 

https://t.co/s1Px8Slk4w
text.14:
Universal Health Coverage:
-Enables people to make good health decisions
-Brings life-saving services to rural communities 
-Builds networks to provide affordable, local treatment
-Provides more sophisticated services at hospitals 
https://t.co/wi2ZyM37cl

:white_heavy_check_mark:Eye care services assessment tool

:white_heavy_check_mark:Tool for assessment of rehabilitation services & systems

text.17:
"The #COVID19 pandemic is a crisis unlike anything anyone of us have experienced in our lifetimes. But it must also be a turning point for all of us; a catalyst for making #HealthForAll a reality, and not just an aspiration"-@DrTedros #UNGA  
https://t.co/pJfTAsyLYI
text.18:
"When we promote and protect health, we also promote and protect jobs, businesses, economies, education, gender equality, peace, sustainability and more"-@DrTedros #UNGA #HealthForAll 

https://t.co/pJfTAsyLYI
text.19:
"The policy brief on #COVID19 and Universal Health Coverage is a timely reminder to all nations that investing in health is not an optional extra; it’s the foundation of stable, prosperous & peaceful societies and economies"-@DrTedros #UNGA #HealthForAll 

https://t.co/pJfTAsyLYI
text.20:
"#COVID19 puts at risk many of the health gains we have made in the past 20 years. 

But far from derailing our efforts to achieve universal health coverage, the pandemic must drive us to forge ahead with even more urgency, determination and innovation"-@DrTedros #UNGA
text.21:
"A year on, the #COVID19 pandemic has turned our :globe_showing_Europe-Africa: upside down.

As the policy brief on #COVID19 & Universal Health Coverage says, the pandemic has exposed the inequalities & weaknesses of health systems in all countries"-@DrTedros #UNGA #HealthForAll 

https://t.co/DjSj2RAZB2
text.22:
"The day before that landmark event, the Global Preparedness Monitoring Board launched its first report, warning that the world was unprepared for the next pandemic, and that it was only a matter of when, not if the next pandemic struck"-@DrTedros #UNGA 

https://t.co/hiOHZ1c5n2
text.23:
"One year ago, the nations of the world came together in solidarity to endorse the #UNGA Political Declaration on Universal Health Coverage"-@DrTedros #HealthForAll 

https://t.co/FNYt3PLKLf

text.26:
After a #stillbirth, healthcare staff should:
:teddy_bear: show sensitivity and empathy
:teddy_bear: acknowledge how the parents feel
:teddy_bear: provide clear information
:teddy_bear: understand that the parents may need specific support both in dealing with their loss and in potentially trying to have another baby https://t.co/r2zZzMnZcd

While most people with vision impairment are over the age of :keycap_digit_five::keycap_digit_zero:, vision loss can affect people of all ages.

Take care of your eyes, change your lifestyle!

text.31:
Despite advances in health services to prevent or treat causes of child death, progress in lowering the #stillbirth rate has been slow. From 2000 to 2019, the annual rate of :down-right_arrow_selector: in the stillbirth rate was just 2.3%.
 
:backhand_index_pointing_right: https://t.co/vgD9SJSzCK https://t.co/kUt0EMNk8p
text.32:
#COVID19 is eroding decades of progress made towards universal health coverage.

We need to invest in stronger health systems now to ensure that everyone can access to health care without experiencing financial hardship. https://t.co/0SFoJoNKJ2
text.33:
Today is #WorldSightDay:eye_selector:

More than :keycap_digit_two: billion people have a vision impairment or blindness and at least :keycap_digit_one: billion of those could have been prevented or has yet to be addressed.

:backhand_index_pointing_right:https://t.co/VQiKlheR6a #HopeInSight https://t.co/oPOKeHyewe

text.35:
Over 40% of stillbirths occur during labour. A #stillbirth could be avoided with access to a trained health worker at childbirth and timely emergency obstetric care.
 
:backhand_index_pointing_right: https://t.co/vgD9SJSzCK https://t.co/VUA9kiiB34
text.36:
A #stillbirth is often due to poor quality of care during pregnancy and birth. Lack of investments in antenatal and intrapartum services and in strengthening the nursing and midwifery workforce are :key: challenges
 
:backhand_index_pointing_right: https://t.co/vgD9SJSzCK https://t.co/Be3XB7pKBw

A #stillbirth is defined as a baby born with no signs of life at 28 weeks of pregnancy or more.
 
:backhand_index_pointing_right: https://t.co/vgD9SJSzCK https://t.co/Mkv9XQwqcp
text.44:
According to :NEW_button: estimates, almost 2 million babies are stillborn every year – or 1 #stillbirth every 16 seconds.
 
#COVID19 related health service disruptions could worsen the situation, potentially adding 200,000 more stillbirths over a 12-month period:
:backhand_index_pointing_right:https://t.co/vgD9SJSzCK https://t.co/4fFAlbrIjj
